Package ohos.data.resultset

Interface SharedResultSet

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ResultSet
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbsSharedResultSet

    public interface SharedResultSet
extends ResultSet
    Provides methods for accessing a database result set obtained by querying the database across processes.

    This class extends the ResultSet class. Some methods in this class are implemented by the abstract class AbsSharedResultSet.

    Since:
    3
    See Also:
    AbsSharedResultSet
    SystemCapability
    SystemCapability.Data#DATA_APPDATAMGR

      • getBlock

        SharedBlock getBlock​()
        Obtains a block from the SharedResultSet.

        The block contains some data of the SharedResultSet.

        Returns:
        Returns the block if it is found; returns null otherwise.
        Since:
        3

      • fillBlock

        void fillBlock​(int startRowIndex,
               SharedBlock block)
        Adds the data of a SharedResultSet to a SharedBlock.

        This method is used to add the data of a SharedResultSet (starting from the startRowIndex position) to a SharedBlock until all data of the SharedResultSet is added to the SharedBlock or the SharedBlock space is insufficient.

        Parameters:
        startRowIndex - Indicates the index in the SharedResultSet. The index starts from 0, indicating the first row.
        block - Indicates the block whose data is to be added to the SharedResultSet.
        Since:
        3

      • onGo

        boolean onGo​(int oldRowIndex,
             int newRowIndex)
        Called when the position of the result set changes.

        When the result set is moved to a new position, this method is called to notify the child class of the move result. If false is returned, the result set will be moved to the beforeFirst position.

        Parameters:
        oldRowIndex - Indicates the original position of the result set.
        newRowIndex - Indicates the new position of the result set.
        Returns:
        Returns true if the result set is moved successfully; returns false otherwise.
        Since:
        3
